# Angular Service Rules

- Use `@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })` by default.
- Type all `HttpClient` requests with generics (`get<T>()`, `post<T>()`, etc.).
- Handle HTTP errors with `catchError` and user-facing notifications.
- Add caching with `shareReplay` or signals when data is reused.

```typescript
// BAD
getUsers() {
  return this.http.get('/api/users');
}
```

```typescript
// GOOD
getUsers() {
  return this.http.get<User[]>('/api/users').pipe(
    shareReplay({ bufferSize: 1, refCount: true }),
    catchError((error) => {
      this.notifications.error('No se pudo cargar usuarios');
      return throwError(() => error);
    })
  );
}
```

Prefer small, focused services and keep side effects explicit.
